# Documentation — keep markdown current

After any agent session that changes behavior, APIs, architecture, env vars,
scripts, or developer setup, update the affected docs in the **same turn** —
do not leave docs for a follow-up pass.

## What to update (check each)

- Workspace `README.md` (this package) when local run/test commands or
  responsibilities change.
- Root `README.md` when quickstart, repo layout, architecture diagram,
  workspaces, or known limitations change.
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` when modules, data flow, RPC contract, testing strategy,
  or production differences change — including sequence diagrams.
- `build-process.md` Decision Log / phase notes when a real trade-off is made
  (ORM, Docker scope, domain siloing, test runner, etc.).
- `DEMO.md` only if the interview walkthrough steps change.

## Rules

- Prefer editing existing sections over appending duplicate "also…" notes.
- Never invent features in docs that the code does not implement.
- If a change is internal-only (refactor with identical public behavior),
  skip docs and say so briefly in the response.
- Do **not** edit plan files under `.cursor/plans/` unless the user asks.
